5:
...Kugui. I don't think I can go back to
paper and paint...
12:
I can't believe we suffered all those
spills and redos when we could've
had this the whole time...
16:
The only problem is it sometimes
freezes, and you lose everything.
19:
You could spend hours on a piece,
and a single mistake by the
machine could make it vanish
without a trace.
23:
...I think I'll stick with paper and paint
after all!
26:
Other worlds can be so different,
huh? Even down to how people
express themselves.
29:
Oh, this book is super thin. Is it a
comic of some kind?
34: I-I don't think you should read that!
38:
Ooooh, it's one of THOSE! Master
drew something like it before!
41:
He really creates whatever he
wants, doesn't he...
45:
Judging by just the cover, whoever
drew this is really good at art.
54: Yeah! Gotta study what I can, right?
57:
Aw, it's not pervy at all. It's also not
really romantic? The whole thing
screams "friendship all the way"!
60:
Why do you sound disappointed
about that?
63:
...This is really impressive, though the
characters remind me a lot of
certain people we know.
66:
Created by Merry Sheep... That can't
be the artist's real name, right?
74: Stella? Sorry, were we being too loud?
77:
No. I'm recruiting people who can
draw.
84:
Hehe... Ehehe... Hehehehe... I've got
one, two, three... more deadlines... If I
have to do another rough drawing,
I'm going to lose it.
96:
Two actual artists? Skilled artists?
Right here? Willing to help? Am I
dreaming?
100:
Uh... Maybe you should get some
sleep first.
105:
You think I have time to sleep? Both
of you, sit down!
114:
I made you do all that... without
explaining anything... At least
everything was for all ages...
118:
I-it's all right. We learned a lot
from helping you.
121:
Yeah, exactly! That was my first time
using those materials and drawing
those types of subjects!
125:
I'm honestly super impressed by
your creativity.
127:
Most of my experience is drawing
things as they are, or just imagining
a single scene!
130:
You showed me how much more I
could be doing!
135:
I-I'm not sure you should be learning
from me... N-not that you can't! I'm
just... doing whatever I want, so like...
139:
Actually, you just gave me the
greatest idea!
142:
I should just draw the rest of KoiAzu's
story myself!
147:
You're going to continue from where
the canon content left off, even
though it's an ongoing series?!
150:
Is that a problem? Master's drawn a
lot of that kind of stuff before for
other series, though.
155:
The people of Yamato are crazy...
But I'm the one who led YOU down
this path... This is my fault!
159:
Th-the most important takeaway is
that you figured out the type of
content you want to try, Ryouki.
161:
Although I'd suggest going with a
different subject matter...
165:
Oh, I know! How about doing the
adventures of Champion Claire?
169:
That's a champion from way before
Light's time, right? I guess that's less
of a legal risk...
172:
Wait, that reminds me. Stella and
Lilith said they added to our
archives...
176:
They sure did! There's more books
here than before!
179:
Ohhh, where should I start? What
should I draw?
183:
R-Ryouki, those books are
important! You should handle them
with more care.
187:
Hmm... So we just have to make a
manuscript of this using our art,
right?
198: Now to turn art into reality!
203:
Heheheh! I had perfect control over
my power just then! All that hard
work paid off!
207:
Huh... So you mashed together all
sorts of ideas and went wild.
210:
I like it! Now you're starting to get
what it means to be an artist!
214:
Hehe, you've improved so much. I'll
have to work hard so you don't
leave me behind.
218:
Aw, shucks. I didn't get THAT good!
But I definitely did improve.
223: What should we paint next, Kugui?
226:
There's so much I wanna do that I
don't know where to start!
